tions. Tweedale shows how these beliefs became popular among Western elites in the early modern period and eventually resulted in the distinctly Western doctrine of progress. This doctrine, an almost religious faith in the capacity of science and technology to improve human life, released economic expansion from traditional constraints and has led to our current environmental emergency. Exploring sources from philosophy, religion, and the history of ideas, Making Wonderful is for all readers who are intellectually curious about the roots of our eco-catastrophe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEcologyxPhilosophy. 0aEnvironmental disasters. 0aHuman ecology. 0aReligion and science. 4aEnvironment. 4aHistory. 4aPhilosophy. 4aSocial Sciences / Religious Studies. 4aSocial Sciences. 70(DE-588)4043207-50(DE-627)1044349100(DE-576)209054700aÖkologie2gnd 70(DE-588)4043208-70(DE-627)1062107500(DE-576)209054719aSozialökologie2gnd 70(DE-588)4205529-50(DE-627)1051348990(DE-576)210169370aTheoretische Ökologie2gnd 70(DE-588)4307790-00(DE-627)1235193140(DE-576)211100250aBionomie2gnd 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh  aBuddhism.  aConfucianism.  aPlato.  aSocratic ethics.  aStoicism.  aZoroastrianism.  aapocalypticism.  acities.  acivilization.  aconsumerism.  ahedonist utilitarianism.  aideology of the West.  ainstrumental rationality.  amillenarianism.  aorigins.  autopias.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packagez978311143542840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212659440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781772126594423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781772126594